.TH "vmcore_alloc_buf" 9 "vmcore_alloc_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmcore_alloc_buf \- allocate buffer in vmalloc memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" vmcore_alloc_buf
.BI "(size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If CONFIG_MMU is defined, use \fBvmalloc_user\fP to allow users to mmap
the buffer to user-space by means of \fBremap_vmalloc_range\fP.

If CONFIG_MMU is not defined, use \fBvzalloc\fP since \fBmmap_vmcore\fP is
disabled and there's no need to allow users to mmap the buffer.
